p.s:
Fifteen days Galaor abode in the monastery before his wounds were healed;
                  then he departed,
                  and rode where chance guided him.

You are not such that you ought to see what goes there;
                  and, if you persist,
                  you must do battle with us.

He answered, Lady, I rejoice to obey rather than displease
                     you;
                  and entered the Castle.

and with that he laced his helm;
                  but his shield he could not take,
                  because of the press there was upon him.

That, quoth she, they will never consent to;
                  but do you return here at a year’s
                     end,
                  and I will have the other two
                     champions
                  ready.

--When I set the lions loose to
                  save you by my young Lady’s order;
                  for she pitied you:
                  if she live, she will be without peer
                  for wisdom as well as beauty.
